0.text: Bug 7752  Export multiple files with same file name under different directories to zip file fails..

2.text: Launch WSWB and create two projects 2.

3.text: Under each project, create a new file with the same name (such as "foo.txt") 3.

4.text: From the main-menu, Select File -> Export  and select Zip File to export 4.

5.text: In the "Export" dialog window, Select both projects created earlier, give  the zip file a name (such as test.zip) and begin export to zip file.

6.text: Results: An error message box pops up: Problems were encountered during export and the  detail lists the file of the same name in project2 as the problem (i.e.

8.text: If you name foo.txt in project 2 foo2.txt there are no problems.

9.text: Expected Behaviour: The zip file should be able to store files with same name under different  directories.
